backend:

load all the files into mongo db. each collection with file name as key and records of the file as objects

develop a get API which accepts the all the filters as query params. implementation of this api should query mongo db to get the required data.



User UI:

user should be able to select the filename from a dropdown.

upon selection, the corresponding columns in the file should be available as filters for the user to filter data

take the inputs from the user and form a query and execute the query to get desired results.

show the result as list of items in the output